init_text: All of the "#1 Dad" mugs in the world change to show the actual ranking of Dads suddenly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I told my father that I did not know what happened and that I would go back to the store to get a new mug.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I went to the store and asked the clerk if there was anything that could be done.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He started to work harder at his job and he came home earlier every day.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He even started to cook dinner every night.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I knew it, but he did not.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was so sad and depressed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He had no time to spend with his friends and he even started to lose his hair.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He had become a different man.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I felt like I was losing my father.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We felt that we should have seen the signs and done something about it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I told him that he was the best dad in the world and that he did not have to prove it to anyone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was a great father and I did not need a mug to tell me that.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He smiled and hugged me and told me that he loved me.
